The Oyo State House of Assembly, yesterday, approved the dissolution of the 33 local government chairmen and 35 chairmen of Local Council Development Areas (LCDAs) in the state. The house said the conduct of the elections by the Oyo State Independent Electoral Commission (OYSIEC) in May 2018 was unconstitutional. The issue was brought by the Majority leader, Sanjo Adedoyin under ‘Matter of Urgent Public Importance’. Chairman of the Association of LG Chairmen of Nigeria in Oyo State, Prince Ayodeji Abass-Alesiloye had, after Governor Seyi Makinde dissolved the chairmen, described the action as unconstitutional. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Our suspension unconstitutional — Kwara LG chairmen Our suspension is unconstitutional - Kwara LG chairmen Vice chairmen vow showdown over dissolution of LG executives Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin